This paper is about object detection using deep neural networks (DNNs) and focuses on enhancing the performance and energy efficiency of the inference phase of DNNs. This topic falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The paper also discusses hardware implementation on FPGAs, which falls under embedded systems (cs.ET) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a weight quantization framework using optimization techniques, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.AR, cs.ET, cs.SY, and cs.LG.
